.TH CRX-FPM 8 "2023" "The CRX Group" "Scripting Language"
.SH NAME
.TP 15
crx-fpm \- CRX FastCGI Process Manager 'CRX-FPM'
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B crx-fpm
[options]
.LP
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBCRX\fP is a widely\-used general\-purpose scripting language that is especially suited for
Web development and can be embedded into HTML. This is a variant of CRX that will run in the background as a daemon, listening for CGI requests. Output is logged to @crx_fpm_localstatedir@/log/crx-fpm.log.
.LP
Most options are set in the configuration file. The configuration file is @crx_fpm_sysconfdir@/crx-fpm.conf. By default, crx-fpm will respond to CGI requests listening on localhost http port 9000. Therefore crx-fpm expects your webserver to forward all requests for '.crx' files to port 9000 and you should edit your webserver configuration file appropriately.
